  "title": "Quality Inspector (Logistics, Aviation)",
  "description": "<p>Job Summary:</p><p>The incumbent will be part of a larger team within the Logistics department in providing seamless and customer-focused solutions to support the achievement of business objectives. </p><p>What you will be doing:</p><ul><li>Inspect aircraft spares</li><li>Verify aircraft spares to ensure appropriate accompanying documents from the OEMs, vendors and suppliers</li><li>Work on continuous improvement projects to improve work areas and procedures</li><li>Facilitate period audits from civil aviation authorities and customers</li><li>Maintain shelf life records for aircraft spares with limited life</li><li>Monitor and conduct surveillance audits on all stores activities within the bonded stores</li><li>Raise discrepancy reports for any discrepancies found on any aircraft spares in the bonded stores</li></ul><p>The successful candidate:</p><ul><li>Work experience in the aviation industry would be an advantage </li><li>CAAS M10/ L11 /L12 would be an advantage </li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office and presentation skills </li><li>Excellent interpersonal and influencing skills </li></ul>",
